Cross-examined by MR. TAYLOR. Q. What does K mean? A. I put that down as my private mark—the house I lodge in belongs to Mr. Rose—three or four people slept in the house one night, and five or six another night—when many people come there many sleep there; it is a lodging-house—when I discovered my loss I went to Mr. Vandenberg, about 4 o'clock in the morning—I went first to Mr. Green, and he told me to go to Mr. Van
denberg, for he knew Mr. Vandenberg mostly bought stolen property, and he knew where to recover such things—I went with Mr. Green to Vanden
berg's;

